"For several years, Katie worked a series of jobs that had no advancement opportunity, little financial security and no benefits. Then, Katie learned about The Excel Center, where she could take courses to earn her high school diploma at an accelerated pace. She decided to enroll and use the on-site child care center to care for her sons while she attended class. In just eight months, Katie earned 42 credits and two industry certifications ‚Äî all at no cost..." #MondayMotivation #ExcelCenter #GoodwillIndy

April 29 at 8:57 PM ¬∑

COVID-19 may have changed the WAY we do things but it can't change the WHY WE DO IT! We do it because WE LOVE OUR STUDENTS and the dedication they put forth everyday to reach their goals. We realize this new way of learning is different and can sometime feel difficult but TOGETHER we will make it. From the Staff of the Michigan Street Excel Center to each and every one of our students, We MISS You all and just wanted to send some encouragement your way. We're ROOTING FOR YOU to KEEP GOING! YOU GOT THIS! Hang in there and know WE ARE ALWAYS HERE FOR YOU!
We are PROUD to say "Our Students ROCK!"

post_text:
While no cases of the coronavirus (COVID-19) have been reported at The Excel Center, in an effort to continue to keep our students, staff and families safe all Excel Center schools will be closed starting Friday, March 13 through Friday, March 20, 2020. Spring Break will take place as scheduled March 23 - April 3. All Excel Center schools plan to resume classes on Monday, April 6*.

We realize that these changes may create challenges for some; however, the safety of our students and employees is our first priority. We continue to monitor and assess guidelines from U.S. Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC), the World Health Organization (WHO), and the Indiana Health Department related to COVID-19, and will provide updates as things unfold.

*In accordance with the Wayne County Health Department, The Excel Center in Richmond, IN will resume classes on Monday, April 13.

Ana Gonzalez not only graduated from The Excel Center Goodwill's Adult High School, but she found she had a passion helping others reach their goal of earning a high school diploma and took a job at The Excel Center after graduation. Pictured with Ana is her Goodwill Guide, Chris. Goodwill Guides act as life coaches and help students overcome their barriers to education. We're so thankful for the perseverance of our students and the Goodwill Guides' willingness to go the extra mile.

We have so much to be grateful for we're taking a whole month to share our gratitude this November. #MonthofGratitude

post_text:
Mohammed was only 18 when his family fled their war-torn country of Syria. Speaking little English, Mohammed enrolled at The Excel Center where he earned his diploma and certification as a Clinical Medical Assistant in under two years. Learn more about Mohammed's journey at RTV6 (WRTV - Indianapolis).

https://www.theindychannel.com/news/hiring-hoosiers/refugee-escapes-war-builds-new-life-in-indianapolis?fbclid=IwAR3E-adPkRTPRgcd1Y9OZNXPfoIPpfBT6sn4Yhz9D5HtGVKTJhGmWXF94U0

post_text:
#TestimonialTuesday Briahnna Gray graduated from The Excel Center Noblesville in February 2018. She graduated with a free job certification from The Excel Center with plans to earn an associate degree in physical therapy. At the graduation ceremony, Briahnna was honored with The Giver Award, which the school gives to students who are determined and inspiring. The award recipient was also a student speaker at her graduation ceremony and shared her journey with the community.

Read Briahnna's speech on our Goodwill of Central & Southern Indiana blog at http://bit.ly/2AU6n3E.

post_text:
#TestimonialTuesday Camree Banks graduated from The Excel Center West in February 2018. Through her hard work and perseverance, she was able to overcome various obstacles. Her hard work paid off because she graduated Cum Laude and as a 21st Century Scholar. Camree plans to attend college in the fall to study photography, film and production.

Visit our blog at Goodwill of Central & Southern Indiana to read her story she shared at the graduation ceremony: http://bit.ly/2APIeuU.
